<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> pay attention to someone • pay attentions to someone</xh5><p> <i>pay attention to someone—</i>take notice of smb.; show interest in a person: Hardly anyone of the crew of six <u>paid any attention to</u> the man and teenage boy who had come aboard.</p><p> <i>pay attentions to someone</i>—<i>(also: pay one’s attentions to someone)</i> court a woman in the hope of winning her affections: The newspapers report that at the moment he is <u>paying his attentions to</u> an Italian countess.</p> </entry>
